📊 Sales Dashboard – Power BI
This project showcases a comprehensive Sales Dashboard built using Power BI, designed to provide actionable insights into key sales metrics, customer behavior, and product performance.

🔍 Overview
The dashboard displays visual analysis across different dimensions such as city, category, customer, payment mode, and product sub-categories. It helps stakeholders quickly grasp business performance and make informed decisions.

📌 Key Features
KPI Cards:

Total Profit: 37K

Total Quantity Sold: 5615

Total Sales Amount: 438K

Visual Insights:

Profit by City: Highlights top-performing cities like Indore and Pune.

Quantity by Category (Pie Chart): Shows distribution across Clothing, Electronics, and Furniture.

Profit by Category (Bar Chart): Compare profit margins among different product categories.

Quantity by Customer Name: Identify top buyers.

Quantity by Payment Mode (Donut Chart): Analyze payment preferences like UPI, COD, etc.

Profit by Sub-Category: Drill-down into items like Printers, Bookcases, Sarees, etc.

🎯 Purpose
This dashboard helps:

Business managers to track performance.

Sales teams to identify top products and customers.

Marketing teams to tailor strategies based on regions or customer segments.

🛠️ Tools Used
Power BI Desktop,

Data imported from Excel,

DAX for calculated measures.

